# Shortcuts

- Shift-h - show alpha in color
    
- Alt -v - paste attrbutes
    

  
  

# Mask

- Color tab, select power window icon
    
- ![](data:image/png;base64,)
    
- [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dKyd54E3tFw](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dKyd54E3tFw)
    
- If it’s a square crop you’re looking for
    

- In edit mode, top right, inspector tab, go to cropping, and choose the settings
    

- If it’s a complex mask
    

- [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hDXzOv2sONU](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hDXzOv2sONU)
    
- ![](data:image/png;base64,)
    
- Select the node on bottom left, then the rectangle on the top right
    
- You can also select other things for more complex masks
    

  

# Copy properties between clips

- Copy from clip desired (ctrl c)
    
- Select clip to paste attributes, and press alt - v
    
- Select properties and past
